ubuntu-rockchip-settings (2.1.2~resolute) resolute; urgency=medium

  * control: trim ubuntu-desktop-rockchip.Depends to just ubuntu-desktop +
    ubuntu-rockchip-settings. The desktop-preinstalled livecd-rootfs hook
    also runs `apt-get -y purge flash-kernel fwupd`, and listing fwupd as a
    hard Depends caused that purge to cascade-remove ubuntu-desktop-rockchip
    just like the cloud-init case in 2.1.1. Server is unaffected because no
    purge hook runs against it; cloud-init/udisks2/etc. remain Depends of
    ubuntu-server-rockchip.

 -- clsx524 <clsx524@gmail.com>  Sun, 03 May 2026 23:00:00 +0000

ubuntu-rockchip-settings (2.1.1~resolute) resolute; urgency=medium

  * control: drop cloud-init from ubuntu-rockchip-settings.Depends and
    ubuntu-desktop-rockchip.Depends. The desktop-preinstalled livecd-rootfs
    hook does `apt-get -y purge cloud-init` (because desktop uses oem-config
    for first-boot user creation), and the hard Depends caused that purge to
    cascade-remove ubuntu-rockchip-settings and ubuntu-desktop-rockchip,
    leaving the desktop image with no meta-package. cloud-init remains a
    direct Depends of ubuntu-server-rockchip only.

 -- clsx524 <clsx524@gmail.com>  Sun, 03 May 2026 22:30:00 +0000

ubuntu-rockchip-settings (2.1~resolute) resolute; urgency=medium

  * debian/ubuntu-rockchip-settings.install: actually ship etc/cloud and
    usr/lib/u-boot-menu config files (previously the package was empty).
  * 99-rockchip.cfg: pin NoCloud to fs_label CIDATA so cloud-init finds the
    seed without timing out on EC2/Azure/GCE probes.
  * control: add cloud-init, openssh-server, udisks2, fwupd, modemmanager and
    network-manager as explicit Depends on ubuntu-{server,desktop}-rockchip
    so apt-get autoremove (run after kernel install) does not strip them.

 -- clsx524 <clsx524@gmail.com>  Sun, 03 May 2026 19:30:00 +0000

